it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface Class.Equivalent<O,J,D extends Class<O,J>>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the ontology.
    J - the type of Ground and EntitySet managed by this Descriptor.
    D - the type of Class descriptor instantiated during buildEquivalentClasses() through getEquivalentClassDescriptor(Object, Object).
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>, Class<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ClassExpression.Equivalent<D>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FullClassDesc, RestrictionClassDesc
    Enclosing interface:
    Class<O,J>

    public static interface Class.Equivalent<O,J,D extends Class<O,J>>
extends Class<O,J>
    Implementation of this interface enables a Class to have the Class.Equivalent expression.

    • Method Detail

      • readExpressionAxioms

        default java.util.List<Axiom.MappingIntent> readExpressionAxioms()
        Description copied from interface: Axiom.Descriptor
        This method is used to update specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the internal state of the descriptor with the queried OWL structure, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet).
        Specified by:
        readExpressionAxioms in interface Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>
        Returns:
        the changes made in the Axiom.EntitySet during the reading. Note that the elements of the returned list, may not have the Axiom.MappingIntent.getOntologyChanges() field initialised (i.e.: Void).

      • buildEquivalentClasses

        default java.util.Set<D> buildEquivalentClasses()
        Create an Axiom.Descriptor set where each element represents the classes equivalent to this Class. Each of those Classs are instantiated through the method getEquivalentClassDescriptor(Object, Object); this is called for all getEquivalentClasses().
        Returns:
        the set of Classs that describes the entities equivalent to this described ontological class.

      • getEquivalentClassDescriptor

        D getEquivalentClassDescriptor(J instance,
                               O ontology)
        This method is called by buildEquivalentClasses() and its purpose is to instantiate a new Class to represent an class equivalent from this Class Descriptor.
        Parameters:
        instance - the instance to ground the new Class.
        ontology - the ontology in which ground the new Class.
        Returns:
        a new Axiom.Descriptor for all the classes equivalent to this descriptor.

      • getEquivalentClasses

        Returns:
        the entities describing the equivalent classes to this object

      • queryEquivalentClasses

        Axiom.EntitySet<J> queryEquivalentClasses()
        Queries to the OWL representation for the equivalent classes of this class.
        Returns:
        a new EntitySet contained the equivalent classes to the OWL structure of Axiom.Descriptor.getInstance().

      • synchroniseEquivalentClassesToExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseEquivalentClassesToExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet) with queryEquivalentClasses() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed in the OWL representation for synchronise it with respect to getEquivalentClasses(). This should be done by Axiom.Descriptor.writeExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise this structure with the equivalent classes of an OWL class.

      • synchroniseEquivalentClassesFromExpressionAxioms

        default Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<J> synchroniseEquivalentClassesFromExpressionAxioms()
        It calls EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet) with queryEquivalentClasses() as input parameter. This computes the changes to be performed into the getEquivalentClasses() in order to synchronise it with respect to an OWL representation. This is be done by readExpressionAxioms().
        Returns:
        the changes to be done to synchronise the equivalent classes of an OWL class with this structure.
